<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=George_Saunders&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.saunderssaunderssaunders.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.saunderssaunderssaunders.com/" rel="nofollow">Official website</a> at saunderssaunderssaunders.com.</li>
<li><a href="http://www-hl.syr.edu/depts/english/cwp/saunders.htm" class="external text" title="http://www-hl.syr.edu/depts/english/cwp/saunders.htm" rel="nofollow">Staff profiles</a> at Syracuse University website.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/weekend" class="external text" title="http://www.guardian.co.uk/weekend" rel="nofollow"><i>The Guardian Weekend</i> magazine</a>, where Saunders' column <i>American Psyche</i> appears each week.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.georgesaundersland.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.georgesaundersland.com/" rel="nofollow">George Saunders Land</a>, a comprehensive fan website.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.thislife.org/Radio_Episode.aspx?episode=51" class="external text" title="http://www.thislife.org/Radio_Episode.aspx?episode=51" rel="nofollow">Saunders reads "The 400 Pound CEO"</a> on the <i>This American Life</i> radio program.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.guernicamag.com/guest_editors/fiction/06/10/" class="external text" title="http://www.guernicamag.com/guest_editors/fiction/06/10/" rel="nofollow">Saunders editorial</a> about guest-editing <i>Guernica</i> magazine.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.guernicamag.com/interviews/216/dig_the_hole/" class="external text" title="http://www.guernicamag.com/interviews/216/dig_the_hole/" rel="nofollow">Saunders interview</a> in <i>Guernica</i> magazine.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.maximumfun.org/blog/2006/06/podcast-whats-wrong-with-america.html" class="external text" title="http://www.maximumfun.org/blog/2006/06/podcast-whats-wrong-with-america.html" rel="nofollow">Saunders interview</a> on public radio program <a href="/wiki/The_Sound_of_Young_America" title="The Sound of Young America">The Sound of Young America</a>, with bonus reading from <i>In Persuasion Nation</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.powells.com/ink/saunders.html" class="external text" title="http://www.powells.com/ink/saunders.html" rel="nofollow">Hilarious Saunders Q&amp;A</a> at <i>Ink</i> via Powell's Books.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.brassland.org/ahb/writing/archives/2006/05/mean_snacks_and.html" class="external text" title="http://www.brassland.org/ahb/writing/archives/2006/05/mean_snacks_and.html" rel="nofollow">Brief Saunders Q&amp;A</a> upon publication of <i>In Persuasion Nation</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.wnyc.org/flashplayer/player.html#/play/%2Fstream%2Fxspf%2F74200" class="external text" title="http://www.wnyc.org/flashplayer/player.html#/play/%2Fstream%2Fxspf%2F74200" rel="nofollow">Lopate Show</a> with The Story Prize finalists: <a href="/wiki/Rick_Bass" title="Rick Bass">Rick Bass</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mary_Gordon" title="Mary Gordon">Mary Gordon</a>, and <strong class="selflink">George Saunders</strong> (2/27/07)</li>
<li><a href="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=5432052" class="external text" title="http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=5432052" rel="nofollow">Saunders on All Things Considered</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.kcrw.com/etc/programs/bw/bw071227george_saunders" class="external text" title="http://www.kcrw.com/etc/programs/bw/bw071227george_saunders" rel="nofollow">Saunders on KCRW'S The Bookworm</a> discussing <i>The Braindead Megaphone</i>.</li>
<li><a href="http://chiefmag.com/issues/1/features/George-Saunders-on-Faith-Reason/" class="external text" title="http://chiefmag.com/issues/1/features/George-Saunders-on-Faith-Reason/" rel="nofollow">Saunders interview</a> in <i>Chief Magazine</i> discussing morality and religion within contemporary culture.</li>
</ul>


